# Google Sign-In (Google Identity Services)
# 1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 2. Create a project (or pick one you already have)
# 3. "Create Credentials" -> "OAuth client ID" -> Application type: "Web application"
# 4. Under "Authorized JavaScript origins" add: http://localhost:5173
#    (add your production domain too once you deploy)
# 5. Copy the generated Client ID and paste it below
# 6. Copy this file to .env.local and restart `npm run dev`
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=

# Your own self-hosted backend (see /server) — a plain Express + SQLite API
# you run yourself, no third-party database company involved. If this is
# set, it's used instead of Supabase/local storage. Point it at wherever
# you deploy /server, e.g. http://localhost:3001 while developing, or your
# real domain in production. See server/.env.example for the server's own
# setup (JWT_SECRET, admin emails, etc.) and server/README.md to deploy it.
VITE_API_URL=

# Real database (Supabase) — only used when VITE_API_URL above is empty.
# Without either one set, the app runs on a localStorage-only stand-in
# (data stays in this browser, no server).
# 1. Go to https://supabase.com -> New project (free tier)
# 2. Once it's created: Project Settings -> Data API -> copy "Project URL"
#    and the "anon" "public" key (NOT the service_role key)
# 3. Paste them below
# 4. Open the SQL Editor in Supabase, paste the contents of
#    supabase/schema.sql, and run it once — this creates every table,
#    the storage bucket, and the security policies the app expects
# 5. (Optional, for "Sign in with Google") Authentication -> Providers ->
#    Google -> enable it and paste your Google OAuth Client ID (the same
#    one from VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID above) into "Authorized Client IDs"
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
